{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"CONTAINER review (G4 — child consistency), parent c81c (plan-review fan-out optimization). Independent re-walk of the 7 cross-child interaction modes for this child (S5 bin-packing) against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 0250, S2 c6e5, S3 ba7e, S4 98c6, S6 da34) and the parent. NO G4 FINDINGS — clean pairing.\n\n7-mode walk:\n- Implicit shared state: `sizing.py` container-cost projection is shared by S3 (cost-model fix / 2N base + 'container never shed'), S4 (2N->N) and S5 (<N after packing). Real shared state, but EXPLICITLY ordering-resolved by the parent Sequencing note ('Land S3 -> S4 -> S5 STRICTLY in DAG order: S4/S5's sizing.py container-cost projections are only correct AFTER S3's container-never-shed + cost-model fix lands') and the DAG S3->S4->S5. Each landing layers a correct projection on the prior. No contradiction.\n- Conflicting assumptions: S5's Why ('the container still makes one call per child') correctly presumes S4 has landed — matches DAG S4->S5. The ca03 'each child WHOLE / never chunked' invariant is held consistently with the parent Out-of-scope (chunking forbidden) and S4. No conflict.\n- Dependency gap: S5's incoming deps modeled as `blocks` on the blockers — S4 (98c6) blocks 1762 and S6 (da34) blocks 1762 — matching parent DAG S4->S5 and S6->{S4,S5}. Fidelity gate = S6 semantic harness (DEPENDS ON S6), declared. No gap.\n- Scope overlap: S4 and S5 both edit `plan_review_container.md` and `sizing.py`. Strict S4->S5 ordering makes these SERIAL layered edits (S4 adds dual-rubric/attribution + 2N->N projection; S5 adds multi-child sections + required per-child output + <N projection), not concurrent contradictory ownership. The Sequencing note governs the sizing.py seam. Benign under ANTI-FP.\n- Ordering violation: none — S5 is the terminal node of the strict S3->S4->S5 chain and the last to touch the shared projection.\n- Consumer impact: S5's bin-packer reshapes the per-pairing call unit produced by S3's new in-`_run_container` pool + warm-then-fan-out into bins; it CONSUMES (does not contradict) S3's 'container criteria NEVER shed' guarantee and warm-first invariant. Producer->consumer is DAG-ordered. Consistent.\n- Residual references: S5 preserves the EXISTING single-child fallback and the 'too-big -> reduce the ticket' failure finding as unchanged — consistent with the parent ca03 window-fit guarantee; no sibling holds a stale contract against a design S5 removes.\n\nCross-child note (NOT a finding for this pairing): the shared S4/S5/S6 comment flags that the REQUIRED structured per-child output guardrail 'already in S5' must ALSO apply to S4, and that S6's eval should check TAIL-child recall. That is an S4/S6 obligation — S5 already carries the guardrail (its AC requires per-child output) and the S6 eval-gate dependency. So no G4 inconsistency attaches to (parent + S5).\n\nCorroborates the prior container-review comment (1782577558647768001): NO G4 findings."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782578707806028001,"uuid":"03db6bfe-5a63-45ac-ab26-d3e41382fdac"}